{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:proverbs.19",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 19,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 19 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:1",
      "text": "Better is the poor that walketh in his integrity, than he that is perverse in his lips, and is a fool.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:2",
      "text": "Also, that the soul be without knowledge, it is not good; and he that hasteth with his feet sinneth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:3",
      "text": "The foolishness of man perverteth his way: and his heart fretteth against the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:4",
      "text": "Wealth maketh many friends; but the poor is separated from his neighbour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:5",
      "text": "A false witness shall not be unpunished, and he that speaketh lies shall not escape.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:6",
      "text": "Many will intreat the favour of the prince: and every man is a friend to him that giveth gifts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:7",
      "text": "All the brethren of the poor do hate him: how much more do his friends go far from him? he pursueth them with words, yet they are wanting to him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:8",
      "text": "He that getteth wisdom loveth his own soul: he that keepeth understanding shall find good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:9",
      "text": "A false witness shall not be unpunished, and he that speaketh lies shall perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:10",
      "text": "Delight is not seemly for a fool; much less for a servant to have rule over princes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:11",
      "text": "The discretion of a man deferreth his anger; and it is his glory to pass over a transgression.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:12",
      "text": "The king’s wrath is as the roaring of a lion; but his favour is as dew upon the grass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:13",
      "text": "A foolish son is the calamity of his father: and the contentions of a wife are a continual dropping.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:14",
      "text": "House and riches are the inheritance of fathers: and a prudent wife is from the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:15",
      "text": "Slothfulness casteth into a deep sleep; and an idle soul shall suffer hunger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:16",
      "text": "He that keepeth the commandment keepeth his own soul; but he that despiseth his ways shall die.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:17",
      "text": "He that hath pity upon the poor lendeth unto the Lord; and that which he hath given will he pay him again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:18",
      "text": "Chasten thy son while there is hope, and let not thy soul spare for his crying.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:19",
      "text": "A man of great wrath shall suffer punishment: for if thou deliver him, yet thou must do it again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:20",
      "text": "Hear counsel, and receive instruction, that thou mayest be wise in thy latter end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:21",
      "text": "There are many devices in a man’s heart; nevertheless the counsel of the Lord, that shall stand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:22",
      "text": "The desire of a man is his kindness: and a poor man is better than a liar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:23",
      "text": "The fear of the Lord tendeth to life: and he that hath it shall abide satisfied; he shall not be visited with evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:24",
      "text": "A slothful man hideth his hand in his bosom, and will not so much as bring it to his mouth again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:25",
      "text": "Smite a scorner, and the simple will beware: and reprove one that hath understanding, and he will understand knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:26",
      "text": "He that wasteth his father, and chaseth away his mother, is a son that causeth shame, and bringeth reproach.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:27",
      "text": "Cease, my son, to hear the instruction that causeth to err from the words of knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:28",
      "text": "An ungodly witness scorneth judgment: and the mouth of the wicked devoureth iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.19.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:29",
      "text": "Judgments are prepared for scorners, and stripes for the back of fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
